Title: Kac-Moody structure of chiral gravity in the light-cone gauge

Authors: A.Smailagic, Euro Spallucci

Comments: 13 Pages, PhyzzX

Journal-ref: Phys.Lett. B317 (1993) 526-532

We study the residual symmetry $SL(2,R)\otimes U(1)$ of the chiral gravity inthe light-cone gauge. Quantum gravitational effects renormalize the Kac-Moodycentral charge and introduce, through the Lorentz anomaly, an arbitraryparameter. Due to the presence of this free parameter the Kac-Moody centralcharge has no forbidden range of values, and the strong gravity regime is opento investigations.